name: Acomat
description:
Introduction

This canyon is a waterpark playground. The only rappel would be at the end if you do not wish to jump the last waterfall. The rest of the canyon can be slip, walked, or swum through with some easy down climbs. You do not need a wetsuit in this canyon. A very light shorty at best.

Approach

Most beta has you park at the exit and walk up to the start where the river crosses under a bridge. However, you can easily park a shuttle car at the start which would reduce the approach to "0" effort and the canyon to less than an hour.

Descent

Exit

Hike the trail dcl back to the cars.
